Check list of branch :
git branch -a

Create a new branch Develop and switch to the branch :
git checkout -b new branch Develop

switch to the branch Dev2 :
git checkout Dev2

check the status for all files inside the current branch :
git status
You can also handled files with :
use : git add ... to update what will be committed
use git restore ... to discard changes in working directory

To stash your working directory including untracked files (especially those that are in the .gitignore) :
git stash --include-untracked

check the status for all files inside the current branch :
git status

switch to Develop branch
git checkout Develop

check the status for all files inside the current branch :
git status

commit your changement locally :
git commit

push your changement online :
git push
When it's a new branch that you create locally and want to push it to our repository online then you need to :
git push --set-upstream origin Develop
because in this case the current branch Develop has no upstream branch.

write working from top of stash stack
git stash pop
